-- Australia shares higher as upbeat Wall St gives pre-Christmas lift
-- By Byron Kaye
-- Tue Dec 23, 2014 10:22PM EST
-- None



SYDNEY, Dec 24 (Reuters) - Australian shares edged higher on Wednesday as investors took a breather in a shortened Christmas Eve session and falling iron ore prices undercut an upbeat lead from Wall Street reaching a record high. [ID:nL3N0U815O]

After slipping in early trading, the S&P/ASX 200 index <.AXJO> recovered to close up 0.25 percent or 13.58 points at 5394.50. New Zealand's benchmark NZ50 share index <.NZ50> closed 5.32 points higher at an all-time closing high of 5,557.42, also after a shortened session.